<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-3187] PublishEventNotifier - Should not emit events during startup/shutdown and not spawn new events when processing event</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3187</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an event is being send to an endpoint using PublishEventNotifier it may create new events, and so forth. This causes a flood of events.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also further complications occur during start/shutdown of Camel when you send events to routes, which are then being graceful shutdown. Therefore this event notifier should &lt;b&gt;only&lt;/b&gt; publish if camel is fully started and running.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
